        // - For `i < p`, if `s[i] - '0' == k`, assign `colors[i] = '1'`.
        // - For `i >= p`, if `s[i] - '0' == k`, assign `colors[i] = '2'`.
        // The `p` can be `n` (all `k`s go to '1') or `0` (all `k`s go to '2').
