                // The minimum r for a given l is $x+2k+1$.
                // So, for $l_{idx} = x+1$, we can update $min\_r\_for\_l[l_{idx}] = \min(min\_r\_for\_l[l_{idx}], x+2k+1)$.
                // This is not quite right. The problem states $l \leq x < x+2k \leq r$.
                // So, $l$ can be any value from $1$ to $x+1$.
