            // We can pick any point within the valid range.
            // For example, (min_x, min_y) or (max_x, max_y) or (0,0) if within range.
            // The problem statement says "both X and Y should not exceed 10^5 by absolute value".
            // The initial bounds for min_x, max_x, min_y, max_y are large, but they are
            // constrained by robot positions which are within [-10^5, 10^5].
            // So, min_x and max_x will be within [-10^5, 10^5] if a solution exists.
            // Same for y.
            std::cout << 1 << " " << min_x << " " << min_y << "\n";
